title: Planned Unit Developments, Washington DC, 2008
name: Planned Unit Developments, Washington DC, 2008
description:
Planned Unit Developments (PUDs) are zoning designations granted to a specific project at a specific location. PUD approval grants zoning designations that apply specifically to the development, and may expire if not executed within the allotted time frame. In case of such expiration, the zoning reverts back to the underlying zoning. Only approved PUD orders are included in this GIS layer. Some PUDs may have been approved but never built.

All data is stored and exported in Maryland State Plane coordinates NAD 83 meters.

METADATA CONTENT IS IN PROCESS OF VALIDATION AND SUBJECT TO CHANGE.

properties.PUDZONING: R-5-D, R-5-E, SP-2, C-4 and C-3-C
